@startuml
title Sequence Diagram - Use Case: Create Order with Scalability

actor "Mobile App" as APP
participant "LB" as LB
participant "Gateway" as GW
participant "Orchestrator" as ORCH
participant "Order Service" as ORDER
participant "Inventory Service" as INV
participant "Message Broker" as MB
participant "Payment Service" as PAY
participant "Notification Service" as NOTIF

== 1. Request llega ==
APP ->> LB: POST /orders (with JWT)
note left of LB
  LB distribuye a Gateway
  basado en disponibilidad
end note

== 2. Validación y Rate Limiting ==
LB ->> GW: Forward request
GW ->> GW: Validate JWT
GW ->> GW: Check rate limit (100 req/min)
note right of GW
  Si excede límite:
  → 429 Too Many Requests
end note

== 3. Orquestación ==
GW ->> ORCH: POST /orders (decorated request)
activate ORCH
ORCH ->> ORCH: Generar Order ID (UUID)
ORCH ->> ORCH: Crear trace-id para logging

== 4. Consulta paralela ==
par Validaciones paralelas
  ORCH ->> INV: Verificar stock
  activate INV
  INV -->> ORCH: ✓ Stock OK
  deactivate INV
  
  ORCH ->> ORDER: Crear orden (status: PENDING)
  activate ORDER
  ORDER -->> ORCH: Order ID: "ORD-123456"
  deactivate ORDER
end

== 5. Comunicación asincrónica ==
ORCH ->> MB: Publicar "OrderCreated" event
activate MB
note right of MB
  • Topic: orders.created
  • Partition: hash(userId)
  • Timestamp: 2026-01-29T10:30:00Z
  • Retry: 3 intentos
end note

== 6. Procesamiento paralelo (async) ==
par Event Consumers
  MB ->> PAY: Consume "OrderCreated"
  activate PAY
  note right of PAY
    PAY procesa en background
    responde inmediatamente a ORCH
  end note
  
  MB ->> NOTIF: Consume "OrderCreated"
  activate NOTIF
  note right of NOTIF
    NOTIF envía email/push
    sin bloquear flujo principal
  end note
end

== 7. Respuesta inmediata ==
ORCH -->> GW: 202 Accepted\\n(Order queued)
note right of ORCH
  Response rápida al cliente
  Procesamiento continúa en background
end note

deactivate ORCH

GW -->> LB: Forward response
LB -->> APP: 202 + Order ID + polling URL

== 8. Background: Procesamiento ==
par Procesamiento independiente
  PAY ->> PAY: Iniciar proceso pago
  PAY ->> MB: Publicar "PaymentInitiated"
  
  NOTIF ->> NOTIF: Enviar email confirmación
  NOTIF ->> MB: Publicar "NotificationSent"
  
  PAY -->> MB: Publicar "PaymentCompleted"
  MB ->> ORDER: Consume "PaymentCompleted"
  activate ORDER
  ORDER ->> ORDER: Actualizar estado: CONFIRMED
  ORDER ->> MB: Publicar "OrderConfirmed"
  deactivate ORDER
end

== 9. Cliente consulta progreso ==
APP ->> GW: GET /orders/ORD-123456/status
GW ->> ORCH: Forward request
ORCH ->> ORDER: Get order status
ORDER -->> ORCH: status: CONFIRMED
ORCH -->> GW: Response
GW -->> APP: 200 + status: CONFIRMED

deactivate MB
deactivate PAY
deactivate NOTIF

note bottom
  **Demonstrated scalability optimizations:**
  1. ✓ Load Balancing: Distributes load
  2. ✓ Rate Limiting: Protects against floods
  3. ✓ Async Processing: Does not block the client
  4. ✓ Event-Driven: Decoupling
  5. ✓ Parallelization: Simultaneous validations
  6. ✓ Immediate Feedback: 202 Accepted pattern
  7. ✓ Polling URL: Client can monitor progress
  8. ✓ Each service scales independently
end note

@enduml